label: Denison Ranges

label: Diamantina Plain

label: Clarence Lowlands

definition: Ridges and valleys on sandstone and minor metamorphic rocks; rolling country on granite. Bounded by latitudes 22.386559°S and 24.203562°S, and longitudes 146.602107°E and 147.737691°E.

label: East Tasmanian Hills
definition: Fault block hills and mountains on dolerite, sandstone, and mudstone, with granite residuals, ria coast. Bounded by latitudes 40.901944°S and 43.860401°S, and longitudes 146.354357°E and 148.359406°E.

label: East Victorian Uplands
definition: Dissected high plateaus on various resistant rocks, with isolated high plains. Bounded by latitudes 35.300222°S and 38.148959°S, and longitudes 144.986927°E and 149.765915°E.

label: Eastern Upland Division
definition: The eastern uplands of Australia. Landform patterns reflect structural contrasts. Meridional folding and faulting are reflected in a general north–south grain of relief. It includes both the Great Divide and the Great Escarpment. Bounded by latitudes 9.141290°S and 43.860401°S, and longitudes 141.020610°E and 153.638336°E.

label: Fitzroy Uplands Province
definition: Low ranges and tablelands with lowlands and some plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 20.060381°S and 25.991111°S, and longitudes 146.069187°E and 151.600625°E.

label: Great Barrier Reef Province
definition: Erosional plains with sand plains, lakes and alluvial valley floors; breakaways. Bounded by latitudes 9.141290°S and 24.096460°S, and longitudes 141.419143°E and 152.394791°E.

label: Kosciuszkan Uplands Province
definition: Mainly depositional plains around the southeast of the Gulf of Carpentaria. Bounded by latitudes 33.2043171°S and 39.522332°S, and longitudes 141.020610°E and 150.849319°E.

label: Macquarie Uplands Province
definition: Low plateaus, sand plains and dune fields. Bounded by latitudes 30.370879°S and 35.303008°S, and longitudes 147.660206°E and 152.205841°E.

label: New England–Moreton Uplands Province
definition: Adelaide Hills and lowland areas to Broken Hill. Bounded by latitudes 23.974239°S and 32.756200°S, and longitudes 148.175259°E and 153.638336°E.

label: Peninsular Uplands Province
definition: Interior lowlands, mainly internally draining. Bounded by latitudes 9.354060°S and 19.560565°S, and longitudes 141.718155°E and 146.150360°E.

label: Tasmanian Uplands Province
definition: Dissected plateaus and tablelands, some alluvial plains. Bounded by latitudes 39.435318°S and 43.860401°S, and longitudes 143.819443°E and 148.498795°E.

label: Eighty Mile Plain
definition: Coastal plains and dunes with some estuarine plains. Bounded by latitudes 17.842708°S and 20.187084°S, and longitudes 118.807411°E and 122.745733°E.

label: Einasleigh Plains
definition: Undulating to irregular plains on granite and metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 18.002822°S and 19.422524°S, and longitudes 143.803457°E and 144.677042°E.

label: Expedition Scarplands
definition: Rugged plateaus and ridges on sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 23.599106°S and 25.991111°S, and longitudes 148.688263°E and 150.403674°E.

label: Eyre Dunefield
definition: Stable northwest–southeast longitudinal dunes, locally broken by granite hills and ridges of metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 32.373119°S and 33.74147°S, and longitudes 135.14687°E and 137.58727°E.

label: Eyre Peninsula Province
definition: Lowlands and plains sloping to the Gulf of Carpentaria. Bounded by latitudes 29.346210°S and 29.346210°S, and longitudes 131.151728°E and 137.630649°E.

label: Gairdner Plain
definition: Alluvial plains and salt lakes with some dunes. Bounded by latitudes 29.34621°S and 32.333142°S, and longitudes 132.491585°E and 137.630649°E.

label: Gawler–Cleve Ranges
definition: Rounded ranges of acid volcanic rocks and hills of metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 31.457066°S and 32.789524°S, and longitudes 134.814071°E and 137.502419°E.

label: Lincoln Hills
definition: Low granite hills and plains extending as headlands and inlets. Bounded by latitudes 33.599126°S and 35.340549°S, and longitudes 135.027893°E and 136.969757°E.

label: Fitzroy Plains
definition: Floodplains, sandplains, and broad estuarine plains. Bounded by latitudes 16.577756°S and 18.815086°S, and longitudes 123.515999°E and 126.029559°E.

label: Fitzroy Ranges
definition: Scattered tablelands and ranges of sedimentary rocks and extensive outcrop plains and sandplain and east–west longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 18.101217°S and 19.371511°S, and longitudes 123.760104°E and 127.802019°E.

label: Mackenzie–Dawson Lowlands
definition: Floodplains, clay plains and sandy bedrock lowlands. Bounded by latitudes 21.604907°S and 25.447947°S, and longitudes 147.931586°E and 150.648043°E.

label: Nagoa Scarplands
definition: Sandstone strike ridges and clay valleys. Bounded by latitudes 22.7778°S and 25.515761°S, and 146.069187°longitudes E and 148.035313°E.

label: Scartwater Hills
definition: Hills, ridges and valleys on sandstone and minor metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 20.765358°S and 22.208163°S, and longitudes 147.394594°E and 146.158662°E.

label: Springsure–Clermont Plateaus
definition: Moderately dissected low plateaus, mainly basalt with minor sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 22.215523°S and 24.600405°S, and longitudes 147.266649°E and 149.020632°E.

label: Townshend Ranges and Lowlands
definition: Mosaic of mountains, hills, lowlands and peninsulas. Lowlands include alluvial plains, tidal flats and coastal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 20.060381°S and 22.064371°S, and longitudes 149.523331°E and 148.368599°E.

label: Flinders–Lofty Ranges
definition: Complex fold belt of prominent ranges in north, chiefly quartzite with vales on weaker rocks; stepped fault blocks and islands in south, mainly of weathered metamorphic rocks with ferruginous cappings. Bounded by latitudes 29.36382°S and 36.396648°S, and longitudes 136.532745°E and 139.788214°E.

label: Fortescue Valley
definition: Mainly alluvial lowland with hardpan wash plains and sandplain, possibly a graben. Bounded by latitudes 21.574089°S and 23.432007°S, and longitudes 116.768643°E and 120.576764°E.

label: Garnet Uplands
definition: Hilly uplands with dissected greywacke and volcanics in north and undulating country on granite and metamorphic rocks in the south. Bounded by latitudes 15.929353°S and 18.150512°S, and longitudes 143.981117°E and 145.708606°E.

label: Gibson Desert Plains
definition: Sandy or stony ferruginous plains. Bounded by latitudes 22.164247°S and 27.280427°S, and longitudes 123.848425°E and 127.018453°E.

label: Gilbert Hills
definition: Rolling country on granite, and ridges and valleys on metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.768153°S and 18.883566°S, and longitudes 142.838231°E and 143.833715°E.

label: Gippsland Plain
definition: Terraced plains with sand and gravels. Bounded by latitudes 37.66496°S and 38.762749°S, and longitudes 146.356378°E and 149.501251°E.

label: Glengarry Hills
definition: Hills, hardpan wash plains and stony plains on sedimentary, granitic, and volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 24.917901°S and 26.802447°S, and longitudes 118.157898°E and 120.763266°E.

label: Goulburn Corridor
definition: Broad valley floors on weaker rocks, overlooked by irregular dissected plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 32.171759°S and 32.771659°S, and longitudes 149.634664°E and 150.629272°E.

label: North Reefs
definition: Patch reefs with semicontinuous outer barrier. Bounded by latitudes 9.14129°S and 14.22723°S, and longitudes 141.419144°E and 144.063858°E.

label: South Reefs
definition: Patch reefs with bedrock islands and discontinuous outer barrier. Bounded by latitudes 14.05041°S and 24.09646°S, and longitudes 144.202148°E and 152.394791°E.

label: Great Sandy Desert Dunefield
definition: East–west longitudinal dunes and minor salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 17.863681°S and 25.983593°S, and longitudes 119.380411°E and 130.572816°E.

label: Great Victoria Desert Dunes
definition: West–east longitudinal dunes, broken by low tablelands and ridges in the northwest. Bounded by latitudes 25.158119°S and 32.196006°S, and longitudes 122.540793°E and 135.621357°E.

label: Greenough Hills
definition: Dissected ferruginous plateaus and hills of sandstone and shale over granite, extensive sandplain on dissected plateau. Bounded by latitudes 27.376333°S and 28.987°S, and longitudes 113.588676°E and 115.131853°E.

label: Gregory Range
definition: Dissected sandstone plateau and hilly country on acid volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.929322°S and 19.027512°S, and longitudes 142.174496°E and 142.174496°142.978174°E.

label: Gulfs Ranges Province
definition: Outer barrier reef, patch reefs and some high islands. Bounded by latitudes 29.363820°S and 36.396648°S, and longitudes 136.421646°E and 142.138110°E.

label: Olary Spur
definition: Low hill belt of folded crystalline and sedimentary rocks. Bounded by latitudes 31.674194°S and 33.41426°S, and longitudes 139.010067°E and 140.74781°E.

label: Torrens–Gulf Plains
definition: Salt lake and bahadas in north; alluvial and littoral plains in south; northwest–southeast longitudinal dunes, mainly stabilized. Bounded by latitudes 30.025979°S and 35.030416°S, and longitudes 137.205397°E and 138.743677°E.

label: Yorke Peninsula
definition: Undulating lowland of folded crystalline and metamorphic rocks; cover of calcrete and stabilized northwest–southeast longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 33.3832°S and 35.907952°S, and longitudes 136.421646°E and 138.332656°E.

label: Gunnedah Lowland
definition: Alluvial plains, sandstone ridges and hills of basic intrusive rocks. Bounded by latitudes 30.619349°S and 31.74602°S, and longitudes 149.748673°E and 150.600731°E.

label: Halls Creek Ridges
definition: Ranges and rounded hills on sedimentary (and some volcanic) rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.004139°S and 19.099638°S, and longitudes 126.760108°E and 128.833139°E.

label: Hamersley Plateaus
definition: Dissected bold plateaus and ranges of flat lying or moderately folded sandstone, quartzite, and volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 21.576916°S and 23.515019°S, and longitudes 116.080361°E and 120.263465°E.

label: Hawkesbury–Shoalhaven Plateaus
definition: Deeply dissected sandstone plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 32.414976°S and 35.303008°S, and longitudes 149.85788°E and 151.706956°E.

label: Hume Slopes
definition: Ridges and minor tablelands stepping down westwards and breaking into detached hills with intervening alluvial valley floors. Some strong structural control on landforms. Bounded by latitudes 33.204317°S and 36.238821°S, and longitudes 146.159809°E and 148.600195°E.

label: Hunter Valley
definition: Undulating to low hilly country on weak rocks, with alluvial and sandy littoral plains. Bounded by latitudes 31.942578°S and 33.079382°S, and longitudes 150.452434°E and 152.205841°E.

label: Interior Lowland Division
definition: Younger intracratonic basins with relatively flat sedimentary strata. Bounded by latitudes 11.302946°S and 38.411320°S, and longitudes 133.128183°E and 152.319707°E.

label: Murray Lowlands Province
definition: Mountains and plateaus ranging from the highest point in Australia to the coast. Bounded by latitudes 29.957591°S and 38.411320°S, and longitudes 138.723209°E and 148.3885345°E.

label: Israelite Plain
definition: Narrow coastal plain with extensive dunes. Bounded by latitudes 32.926917°S and 34.108841°S, and longitudes 123.498621°E and 124.49038°E.

label: Ivanhoe Plains
definition: Plains with low west–east stabilized longitudinal dunes and sandplain, small pans with lunettes, minor sandstone ridges, floodplains. Bounded by latitudes 31.291259°S and 34.470967°S, and longitudes 139.760816°E and 145.562091°E.

label: Jardine Uplands
definition: Locally dissected rolling sandstone upland with transgressive coastal dunes along eastern margin. Bounded by latitudes 10.86809°S and 12.808629°S, and longitudes 141.718155°E and 143.244873°E.

label: Kennedy Range
definition: Dissected sandstone plateau with partial ferruginous cappings, covered by longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 24.082236°S and 24.974937°S, and longitudes 114.76144°E and 115.231334°E.

label: Kimberley Plateau
definition: Sandstone plateaus (deeply dissected in places) with tabular high summits; some basaltic plateau; ria coast and islands to the northwest. Bounded by latitudes 13.93137°S and 17.828259°S, and longitudes 123.547882°E and 128.233673°E.

label: Kimberley Province
definition: Hilly and mountainous, high relief. Bounded by latitudes 13.689230°S and 19.371511°S, and longitudes 122.091850°E and 128.948688°E.

label: Napier Limestone Ranges
definition: Limestone tableland and intricately dissected bevelled ridges; separated by plains and rocky karst surfaces with box valleys. Bounded by latitudes 16.85309°S and 18.776871°S, and longitudes 123.802612°E and 126.379111°E.

label: Richenda Foothills
definition: Rounded hills and ridges and lowlands on a belt of granite and folded metamorphic and sedimentary rocks with minor basalt. Bounded by latitudes 15.5098°S and 18.099116°S, and longitudes 123.151871°E and 126.579422°E.

label: Springvale Foothills
definition: Granitic, volcanic, and sedimentary hills with minor undulating plains. Bounded by latitudes 16.676474°S and 18.984041°S, and longitudes 126.225017°E and 128.479206°E.

label: Wunaamin Miliwundi and Durack Ranges
definition: Prominent ranges of dipping volcanic and granitic rocks and sandstones rimming the main Kimberley Plateau. The name of this physiographic region was changed from Leopold–Durack Ranges following the renaming of the King Leopold Ranges to Wunaamin Miliwundi Ranges in 2020. Bounded by latitudes 15.528314°S and 18.727432°S, and longitudes 124.447889°E and 128.948688°E.

label: Monaro Fall
definition: Deeply dissected steeply sloping plateau margin in metamorphics and granite. Bounded in the west by the Great Escarpment. Bounded by latitudes 34.924032°S and 37.756359°S, and longitudes 149.336751°E and 150.849319°E.

label: Monaro Tableland
definition: Undulating upland plains with some tabular basalt relief and granite tors. Bounded by latitudes 35.97531°S and 37.778511°S, and longitudes 148.442004°E and 149.431793°E.

label: South Victorian Uplands
definition: Low fault blocks, mainly of tilted and dissected sandstone; granite hills and islands, in two parts either side of Port Phillip Bay. Bounded by latitudes 37.991314°S and 39.522331°S, and longitudes 143.134495°E and 147.030334°E.

label: Tinderry–Gourock Ranges
definition: High hill chains of granite, sandstone and greywacke, moderately dissected, some fault lines. Bounded by latitudes 35.256032°S and 36.690353°S, and longitudes 149.140357°E and 149.709269°E.

label: Werriwa Tablelands
definition: Upland plains with separating strike-aligned hills, closed lake basins. Bounded by latitudes 34.465318°S and 35.654329°S, and longitudes 148.750323°E and 150.152407°E.

label: West Victorian Plains
definition: Plains mainly on basalt lavas with many volcanic forms and lakes, partly on weak sedimentary rocks. Bounded by latitudes 37.412111°S and 38.688694°S, and longitudes 141.282568°E and 145.248168°E.

label: West Victorian Uplands
definition: Moderately high plateaus and strike ridges. Bounded by latitudes 36.207532°S and 38.426071°S, and longitudes 141.02061°E and 145.220636°E.

label: Lakes Plateau
definition: High dolerite plateau with many lakes, glaciated in west. Bounded by latitudes 41.539578°S and 42.440651°S, and longitudes 146.10101°E and 147.345993°E.

label: Laura Plain
definition: Soft sedimentary rock lowlands, alluvial plains and coastal plain. Bounded by latitudes 13.767155°S and 15.767124°S, and longitudes 143.425719°E and 144.74613°E.

label: Leemans Sandplain
definition: Sandplain with some gravel plains, mesas, and small salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 26.492127°S and 30.662666°S, and longitudes 121.492232°E and 123.932368°E.

label: Leeuwin Peninsula
definition: Narrow granitic horst ridge with calcareous dune system on western margin and dissected ferruginous plateau in the east. Bounded by latitudes 33.530159°S and 34.38374°S, and longitudes 114.975029°E and 115.193681°E.

label: Little Sandy Desert
definition: East–west longitudinal dunes and minor salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 22.197759°S and 25.806083°S, and longitudes 119.890907°E and 123.269001°E.

label: Liverpool–Barrington Plateaus
definition: Dissected basaltic plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 31.348304°S and 32.323859°S, and longitudes 151.122234°E and 152.52866°E.

label: Lower Darling Plain
definition: Floodplain and lunette lakes. Bounded by latitudes 29.957591°S and 34.276252°S, and longitudes 140.654329°E and 146.268179°E.

label: Macdonald Sandplain
definition: Mainly sandplain with dune-fringed salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 23.080796°S and 23.766894°S, and longitudes 128.483625°E and 131.01078°E.

label: Macleay–Barrington Fall
definition: Plateau flank dissected into narrow strike ridges and valleys. Bounded by latitudes 30.320413°S and 32.7562°S, and longitudes 150.880601°E and 153.130187°E.

label: Merriwa Plateau
definition: Rolling basalt upland with sandstone cliffs. Bounded by latitudes 31.530666°S and 32.28168°S, and longitudes 149.541224°E and 151.203041°E.

label: Mitchell Slopes
definition: Tablelands stepping down to west and breaking into detached hills. Bounded by latitudes 30.370879°S and 34.812456°S, and longitudes 147.660206°E and 150.043234°E.

label: Warrumbungle Peaks
definition: Dissected volcanic pile with plugs. Bounded by latitudes 30.941727°S and 31.553229°S, and longitudes 148.737898°E and 149.26379°E.

label: Mallee Dunefield
definition: Fixed west–east calcareous longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 33.819057°S and 36.306182°S, and longitudes 139.157554°E and 143.832952°E.

label: Maryborough Lowland
definition: Lowland on weak sedimentary rocks, partly dune covered including K'gari (formerly Fraser Island). Bounded by latitudes 24.144118°S and 26.481847°S, and longitudes 151.764481°E and 153.358566°E.

label: Midlands Plain
definition: Fault-bounded lowland (graben) on weathered sediments, with some dolerite, sedimentary and metamorphic hills. Bounded by latitudes 41.063358°S and 42.191972°S, and longitudes 146.48604°E and 147.55712°E.

label: Millicent Plain
definition: Parallel dune limestone ridges with intervening swamps; closed karst depressions and young volcanoes in southeast. Bounded by latitudes 36.374543°S and 38.41132°S, and longitudes 139.670547°E and 141.670883°E.

label: Moreton Lowland
definition: Lowland on weak sedimentary rocks, with prominent volcanic plugs, includes dune islands. Bounded by latitudes 26.613991°S and 28.19735°S, and longitudes 152.838542°E and 153.579895°E.

label: Murchison Plateau
definition: Sandplains and hardpan wash plains with outgoing drainage and salt lakes, broken by ridges of metamorphic rocks and granite. Bounded by latitudes 25.167211°S and 29.930099°S, and longitudes 115.212771°E and 122.928611°E.

label: Riverine Plain
definition: Alluvial plain. Bounded by latitudes 32.532551°S and 36.949484°S, and longitudes 142.826891°E and 146.761128°E.

label: West–Turkey Plains
definition: Plains with variable dune cover, claypans, saline swamps, and intermittent lakes in low-lying areas. Bounded by latitudes 31.813614°S and 34.798565°S, and longitudes 139.082269°E and 142.942363°E.

label: Wimmera Plain
definition: Eolian and alluvial sandplain, minor low sandstone ridges. Bounded by latitudes 35.255883°S and 37.299233°S, and longitudes E and 140.352986°143.308516°E.

label: Nandewar Peaks
definition: Dissected volcanic pile. Bounded by latitudes 29.543995°S and 30.836196°S, and longitudes 149.760031°E and150.381189°E.

label: Taroom Hills
definition: Sandstone ridges and shale lowlands. Bounded by latitudes 24.56042°S and 26.835811°S, and longitudes 148.175259°E and 151.344084°E.

label: Tenterfield Plateau
definition: Undulating granitic plateau with higher residuals including basalt cappings. Bounded by latitudes 28.190536°S and 31.613426°S, and longitudes 150.916329°E and 152.900874°E.

label: Toowoomba Plateau
definition: Basaltic plateau terminating southeast in dissected volcanic pile (Mount Warning). Bounded by latitudes 25.993017°S and 28.967651°S, and longitudes 151.19928°E and 153.638336°E.

label: Newcastle Ranges
definition: Rugged hills on acid volcanic, granite and metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.141193°S and 19.560565°S, and longitudes 143.368822°E and 144.468041°E.

label: North Australian Plateaus Province
definition: Low ranges, plateaus, tablelands and plains. Bounded by latitudes 10.903421°S and 18.623043°S, and longitudes 127.709584°E and 136.984985°E.

label: Ord–Victoria Plateaus
definition: Dissected plateaus, mainly basaltic but partly of sandstone with local ferruginous cappings. Bounded by latitudes 13.216329°S and 18.623043°S, and longitudes 127.709584°E and 132.195317°E.

label: Pine Creek Ridges
definition: Rounded ridges of folded metamorphic rocks with granitic plains and minor quartzite plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 12.591672°S and 14.301195°S, and longitudes 130.807472°E and 132.975587°E.

label: Top End Coastal Plains
definition: Dissected ferruginous lowlands and minor islands; part alluvial, part estuarine coastal plains. Bounded by latitudes 10.903421°S and 15.936886°S, and longitudes 127.780453°E and 136.984985°E.

label: Whirlwind Plain
definition: Alluvial plain, mainly clay. Bounded by latitudes 14.56509°S and 16.421499°S, and longitudes 129.498352°E and 130.92762°E.

label: North West Cape Ridges
definition: Low ridges and peninsula formed by folded limestone and sedimentary rocks; sandy plains. Bounded by latitudes 21.78509°S and 23.516084°S, and longitudes 113.627853°E and 114.400577°E.

label: North West Ramp
definition: Incised basalt ramp including coastal scarp, with some mudstone and weathered granite. Bounded by latitudes 40.925171°S and 41.55931°S, and longitudes 145.480141°E and 146.594074°E.

label: Northam Slopes
definition: Flat-floored valleys of moderately incised oceanward drainage; older ferruginous remnants with breakaways on divides in east; stripped granite on valley sides in west. Bounded by latitudes 30.27922°S and 34.302188°S, and longitudes 115.978955°E and 117.780392°E.

label: Nullagine Hills
definition: Dissected flat-topped hills of granitic, volcanic, and metamorphic rocks; interspersed by stony plains on granite. Bounded by latitudes 20.521125°S and 23.593862°S, and longitudes 116.080864°E and 121.413178°E.

label: Nullarbor Plain Province
definition: Plateaus, hills and ridges on resistant rocks, with some valley floors. Bounded by latitudes 28.892723°S and 34.108841°S, and longitudes 123.316086°E and 132.708298°E.

label: Roe Plain
definition: Coastal limestone plain with extensive dunes. Bounded by latitudes 31.675752°S and 32.321461°S, and longitudes 125.893166°E and 128.995019°E.

label: Onslow Plain
definition: Alluvial, deltaic, and littoral plains; some sandplain and coastal dunes; minor islands. Bounded by latitudes 20.35881°S and 22.594877°S, and longitudes 114.303879°E and 116.146432°E.

label: Palmerville Hills
definition: Granitic hills and plateaus and sandstone mesas with intervening plains. Bounded by latitudes 15.588526°S and 16.518965°S, and longitudes 143.465556°E and 144.127454°E.

label: Torres High Islands
definition: Islands and low coastal tablelands of volcanic rocks and granite, with fringing reefs. Bounded by latitudes 9.35406°S and 10.99771°S, and longitudes 141.909393°E and 142.707413°E.

label: Wenlock Uplands
definition: Complex of tablelands and low plateaus with north–south lowlands, including the Great Escarpment, and coastal hills in the east. Bounded by latitudes 12.34867°S and 14.030618°S, and longitudes 142.810422°E and 143.598434°E.

label: Pilbara Province
definition: Coastal and alluvial plains, plateaus, scarps, and low hills. Bounded by latitudes 20.014311°S and 27.020391°S, and longitudes 114.943213°E and 123.619433°E.

label: Redvers Dunefield
definition: East–west longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 22.159016°S and 23.233663°S, and longitudes 127.599033°E and 131.672497°E.

label: Rudall Tablelands
definition: Dissected low sandstone tablelands with hills and ranges on gneiss and intervening areas of sandplains. Bounded by latitudes 21.424074°S and 23.726928°S, and longitudes 121.341582°E and 123.566975°E.

label: Salmon Gums Plain
definition: Flat to undulating plain with salt lakes and occasional granitic low hills. Bounded by latitudes 32.246049°S and 33.6694°S, and longitudes 120.450452°E and 123.671862°E.

label: Sandland Province
definition: Higher uplands falling to the east coast. Bounded by latitudes 17.842708°S and 32.196006°S, and longitudes 118.807411°E and 135.621357°E.

label: Stansmore Dunefield and Ranges
definition: East–west longitudinal dunes locally broken by narrow sandstone ranges. Bounded by latitudes 19.052684°S and 22.215138°S, and longitudes 125.851631°E and 128.367324°E.

label: Sturt Creek Floodout
definition: Floodout with distributary channels and claypan. Bounded by latitudes 19.560462°S and 20.325222°S, and longitudes 127.028081°E and 127.706658°E.

label: Shark Bay Peninsulas
definition: Peninsulas, islands, and hinterland formed on indurated limestone dunes; sandplain, dunes and calcrete plains. Bounded by latitudes 25.480511°S and 26.954729°S, and longitudes 112.921501°E and 114.781437°E.

label: Southern Goldfields Plateau
definition: Undulating plains with some sandplains, ferruginous breakaways; ridges of metamorphic rocks and granitic hills and rises; calcretes, large salt lakes and dunes along valleys. Bounded by latitudes 29.016662°S and 32.662586°S, and longitudes 117.411349°E and 124.341387°E.

label: Swan Plain
definition: Dune ridges (on limestone along the coast) and inner alluvial plain. Bounded by latitudes 30.117897°S and 33.79439°S, and longitudes 114.970154°E and 116.059826°E.

label: West Tasmanian Ridges
definition: Ridges of folded quartzite and conglomerate, glaciated in places, parallel valleys on weaker rocks. Bounded by latitudes 40.71249°S and 43.742649°S, and longitudes 144.911068°E and 146.760988°E.

label: Warren–Denmark Slopes
definition: Ferruginous plateau, increasingly dissected in the south, exposing on granite and gneiss; finally merging into narrow swampy plain and coastal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 33.878074°S and 35.13485°S, and longitudes 115.748125°E and 17.768831°E.

label: Western Coastlands Province
definition: Hills and plains, alluvial plains, some dunes and lakes. Bounded by latitudes 20.3588104855°S and 34.5421327617°S, and longitudes 112.921501077°E and 116.152210277°E.

label: Yanrey–Cane Plains
definition: Sandplain and south–north longitudinal dunes with intervening alluvial plains. Bounded by latitudes 21.025096°S and 23.364644°S, and longitudes 114.285043°E and 116.138486°E.

label: Yaringa Sandplain
definition: Sandplain with minor dunes; some stony plains. Bounded by latitudes 22.986782°S and 28.419387°S, and longitudes 113.77167°E and 116.15221°E.

label: Western Plateau Division
definition: Mosaic of shield blocks and intracratonic basins; plains, plateaus, ranges, dune fields. Bounded by latitudes 10.9034°S and 36.396648°S, and longitudes 112.921501°E and 142.138110°E.

label: Yilgarn Plateau Province
definition: This province is more-or-less coincident with the Murray sedimentary basin, consisting of flat alluvium with Eolian cover in places. Bounded by latitudes 25.167211°S and 35.193981 °S, and longitudes 115.212771°E and 124.341387°E.

label: Woodramung Hills
definition: Low rounded ridges of folded metamorphics with intervening sandy plains and hardpan wash plains. Bounded by latitudes 27.812263°S and 30.025157°S, and longitudes 115.428416°E and 117.713387°E.
